Egypt  expects to receive $2 billion
from selling 8,000 plots of land in the capitalâ€™s outskirts to
citizens abroad, Housing Minister Mohamed Fathi ElBaradei said
today.  The offer includes 400 plots in Sheikh Zayed City, each
with an area of 800 square metres at a cost of $675 per square
metre and 4,000 plots of 400 square metres each in Badr City at
$250 per square metre, elBaradei said.  Overseas buyers can start registering for the plots at  the
start of next week, elBaradei told reporters in Cairo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
